cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.CC, cs.NI, cs.LG 

This paper deals with information theory and communication, specifically with polar coding over binary discrete memoryless channels. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses the capacity of channels, which falls under the category of cs.SI (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper involves coding and decoding algorithms, which could be classified under cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Finally, the paper discusses the performance of polar codes, which could be considered a machine learning problem and thus could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning).
